{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7806e61a-b171-4f36-a0f2-11384df2cfe9","content":"Here's what's likely wrong and how to fix each:\n\n**1. Exception on `GoToAsync(\"productdetails\")`**\n\nRelative routes to pages not in the Shell visual hierarchy must be explicitly registered:\n\n```csharp\n// In AppShell constructor or MauiProgram.cs\nRouting.RegisterRoute(\"productdetails\", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));\n```\n\n**2. `GoToAsync(\"//products/active\")` — navigates but nothing visible**\n\nThe most likely cause: the `ShellContent` defines the page directly instead of via `ContentTemplate`, so the page instance is reused/cached and never re-renders. Ensure you use a `DataTemplate`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- ❌ Page created once, never refreshed -->\n<ShellContent Route=\"active\">\n    <local:ActiveProductsPage />\n</ShellContent>\n\n<!-- ✅ Use ContentTemplate -->\n<ShellContent Route=\"active\"\n    ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate local:ActiveProductsPage}\" />\n```\n\nAlso override `OnNavigatedTo` (not just the constructor) to refresh data when navigating back to an already-created page.\n\n**3. 3-second startup with 12 pages**\n\nSame root cause — if pages are declared inline in Shell XAML, **all 12 are instantiated at startup**. Switch every `ShellContent` to use `ContentTemplate`:\n\n```xml\n<ShellContent Route=\"page1\"\n    ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate local:Page1}\" />\n```\n\nThis defers page construction until first navigation, dramatically reducing startup time.\n\n---\n\n**TL;DR:** Register non-hierarchy routes with `Routing.RegisterRoute`, and always use `ContentTemplate` on `ShellContent` (fixes both the \"nothing changes\" and the slow-startup problems).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8fd470ee-42fe-4da6-9b28-921dbc858d84","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about three common .NET MAUI Shell navigation issues. These are well-known patterns I can answer directly from knowledge without needing to search a codebase. Let me provide concise, accurate answers.\n\n1. `GoToAsync(\"productdetails\")` throwing an exception — likely the route isn't registered with `Routing.RegisterRoute`.\n2. `GoToAsync(\"//products/active\")` navigates but nothing visible changes — likely the ShellContent's `ContentTemplate` isn't set, or the page doesn't update because it's already created and `OnNavigatedTo`/`OnAppearing` isn't refreshing data. Actually, more likely: the route exists in the visual hierarchy but the Tab/ShellContent doesn't have distinct visual content, OR the issue is that the page is cached and doesn't re-render. Wait — the most common cause is that multiple ShellContents share the same page type or the ContentTemplate isn't properly defined. \n\nThe most likely culprit here is that the page instance is being reused rather than recreated on navigation, so the UI doesn't update even though the route changed — the user needs to implement proper lifecycle handling in `OnNavigatedTo` or `OnAppearing` to refresh the displayed content. I think the real culprit is that Shell caches the page instance after the first navigation, so even though the route changes and `CurrentItem` updates, the page itself isn't recreated—and without lifecycle hooks like `OnAppearing` or `OnNavigatedTo` being properly wired up to refresh the content, the UI appears unchanged.\n\nThe practical fixes come down to two main issues: either the route isn't registered with `Routing.RegisterRoute()` for pages outside the Shell hierarchy, or the `ShellContent` is misconfigured—missing a `ContentTemplate`, not visible, or not properly distinguishing the active tab visually. — the most practical answers are: routes not being registered with `Routing.RegisterRoute`, the page not being properly templated or the visual hierarchy making navigation changes invisible (like when the same Tab is already selected or there's only one ShellContent per Tab), and Shell's eager page creation causing slow startup which can be fixed with lazy loading through `ContentTemplate` and `DataTemplate`.","outputTokens":1888,"requestId":"5021:224BB2:1CF316A:201999E:69FA92F1"},"id":"04ca5ebb-7e91-4f66-852d-d33e5897f2a5","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:02:21.578Z","parentId":"fe7cd5b9-381b-42f4-9a23-0dd6b1708592"}
